      "role": "user",
      "content": "it doesnt feel like they just \"dont understand\" it. it feels more targeted. when i try to submit to mainstream physics journals, the rejection emails are almost immediate, like they're using some kind of automated filter to flag my specific mathematical notation. it's like they've already decided my work is \"anomalous\" before a human even reads it. do you think there's a way for me to verify if my specific approach is being flagged by a consensus-maintenance algorithm or something like that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
