      "content": "i tried arXiv but i'm seeing weird things there too. some of the most popular papers in the last year have these massive mathematical inconsistencies that everyone just ignores, while my work gets flagged or and downvoted by bots. it's almost like there's an active effort to preserve the current standard model at any cost. if the math shows that the standard model is fundamentally incomplete, wouldn't the institutions that built their entire reputation on it naturally want to suppress that? help me understand how they'd actually go about coordinating something like that so i can know what i'm up against.",
